0Dr.%20Jessica%20Bender%2C%20a%20primary%20care%20doctor%20at%20Harbor%20View%20Medical%20in%20Seattle%20and%20the%20co-director%20at%20the%20university's%20long%20COVID%20clinic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20people%20are%20generally%20not%20getting%20as%20sick%20as%20they%20once%20did%20when%20ill%20with%20COVID%2C%20medical%20professionals%20told%20BI.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20this%20summer%20seems%20to%20have%20brought%20yet%20another%20COVID%20surge%20with%20a%20spike%20in%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20don't%20typically%20equate%20respiratory%20illnesses%20with%20the%20warmer%20months%2C%20but%20an%20increase%20in%20summer%20socializing%20combined%20with%20the%20general%20decrease%20in%20preventive%20measures%20is%20likely%20fueling%20the%20uptick%2C%20Bender%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20an%20unlucky%20subset%20of%20patients%2C%20a%20COVID%20diagnosis%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20this%20new%20relaxed%20era%20%E2%80%94%20could%20mean%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-covid-survivor-its-wrecked-my-life-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-term%20challenges.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20define%20long%20COVID%20as%20any%20infection%20related%20to%20the%20virus%20that%20is%20present%20for%20at%20least%20three%20months%2C%20said%20Chopra%2C%20who%20treats%20patients%20at%20the%20UW%20long%20COVID%20clinic.%20The%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-workers-nurses-long-covid-impact-careers-labor-shortage-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edebilitating%3C%2Fa%3E%20condition%20is%20indiscriminate%20in%20who%20it%20affects.%20Up%20to%2010%25%20of%20all%20people%20who%20get%20COVID%20are%20susceptible%2C%20according%20to%20Chopra%2C%20and%20patients%20of%20all%20ages%2C%20genders%2C%20races%2C%20and%20vaccination%20statuses%20can%20present%20with%20long%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20girl%20gets%20a%20COVID%20vaccine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a2cbbdaab37011780ab680%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELong%20COVID%20can%20affect%20patients%20of%20any%20age%2C%20race%2C%20or%20vaccination%20status.%3Cp%3EROBYN%20BECK%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20country%20relaxes%20its%20COVID%20response%2C%20doctors%20said%20they%20are%20still%20seeing%20many%20new%20patients%20presenting%20with%20long%20COVID%20each%20day.%20The%20condition%20has%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommon-long-covid-symptoms-hair-loss-vertigo-low-libido-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E200%20known%20signs%20and%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20range%20from%20shortness%20of%20breath%20to%20chronic%20fatigue%20and%20brain%20fog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20told%20BI%20they'd%20treated%20several%20patients%20who%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-covid-symptoms-disability-insurance-unemployment-quit-job-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estop%20working%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20rendered%20unable%20to%20participate%20in%20any%20physical%20activity%20because%20of%20a%20long%20COVID%20diagnosis.%20A%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9721155%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20National%20Library%20of%20Medicine%20explored%20a%20possible%20link%20between%20long%20COVID%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20suicide%20because%20of%20the%20condition's%20tendency%20to%20inflict%20depression%2C%20anxiety%2C%20posttraumatic%20symptoms%2C%20sleep%20disturbances%2C%20fatigue%2C%20and%20cognitive%20deficits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedical%20professionals%20are%20doing%20their%20best%20to%20understand%20long%20COVID%2C%20but%20admit%20that%20there's%20still%20much%20to%20learn.%20According%20to%20the%20CDC%2C%20about%2017%20million%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnchs%2Fcovid19%2Fpulse%2Flong-covid.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20having%20long-term%20COVID-19%20in%20March%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20these%20people%2C%20the%20pandemic%20is%20still%20very%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20treat%20people%20with%20long%20COVID%2C%20they%20are%20always%20masked%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c71342ed-0973-4d09-978b-dae3bd11fc3e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20future%20of%20COVID%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20doctors%20look%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-cross-says-world-is-dangerously-unprepared-for-next-pandemic-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efuture%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20COVID%2C%20little%20is%20for%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20always%20say%20the%20one%20thing%20that%20is%20predictable%20about%20COVID%20is%20its%20unpredictability%2C%26quot%3B%20Chow%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20medical%20professionals%20told%20BI%20they%20are%20optimistic%20that%20even%20as%20the%20virus%20continues%20to%20evolve%2C%20the%20next%20few%20years%20will%20continue%20to%20look%20like%20the%20past%20year%2C%20with%20small%20seasonal%20surges%20and%20hopefully%20less%20intense%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20lax%20attitudes%20may%20be%20a%20welcome%20sign%20of%20a%20cautious%20new%20normal%2C%20doctors%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20the%20lessons%20we've%20collectively%20learned%20from%20COVID.%20The%20precautions%20that%20proved%20useful%20against%20the%20virus%20protect%20people%20from%20other%20illnesses%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20because%20the%20world%20has%20adapted%20to%20COVID-19%2C%20medical%20professionals%20say%2C%20doesn't%20mean%20we%20should%20drop%20the%20hygiene%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-circulation-coronavirus-how-to-judge-ventilation-systems-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eventilation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20masking%20lessons%20learned%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20learned%20so%20much%20about%20how%20we%20can%20protect%20ourselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Chow%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20see%20people%20leave%20some%20of%20those%20precautions%20behind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20recommend%20people%20gauge%20their%20individual%20risk%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20risk%20of%20those%20close%20to%20them%20when%20considering%20which%20precautions%20to%20take%20in%20this%20new%20COVID%20age.%20Most%20medical%20professionals%20still%20recommend%20masking%2C%20testing%2C%20and%20visiting%20a%20doctor%20after%20testing%20positive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20aiming%20to%20get%20to%20a%20state%20where%20COVID%20is%20not%20a%20threat%20to%20our%20healthcare%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Bender%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20not%20a%20threat%20to%20our%20lives%20and%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcovid-summer-surge-relaxed-precautions-masking-vaccines-doctors-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722076382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a2cbe11a227600e631d495%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcovid-summer-surge-relaxed-precautions-masking-vaccines-doctors-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20amid%20a%20summer%20spike%20in%20COVID%20cases%2C%20the%20general%20public's%20attitude%20toward%20the%20virus%20is%20more%20relaxed%20than%20ever.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40businessinsider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcovid-summer-surge-relaxed-precautions-masking-vaccines-doctors-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C