eft-leaning%20think%20tank%2C%20found%20that%20workers%20in%20the%20South%20earned%20less%20than%20those%20in%20other%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20median%20Southern%20worker%20earned%20%2420.30%20an%20hour%2C%20compared%20to%20%2421.05%20in%20the%20Midwest%2C%20%2422.08%20in%20the%20West%2C%20and%20%2423.81%20in%20the%20Northeast.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20analysis%20found%20that%2022%25%20of%20Southern%20workers%20earned%20less%20than%20%2415%20an%20hour%2C%20compared%20to%2017%25%20in%20the%20Midwest%2C%2012%25%20in%20the%20Northeast%2C%20and%2010%25%20in%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%20pointed%20to%20low%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmap-the-last-time-each-state-raised-its-minimum-wage-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminimum%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-union-membership-fell-lowest-rate-record-2022-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunionization%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Southern%20states%20as%20two%20factors%20keeping%20pay%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20workers%20in%20some%20Southern%20states%20earn%20less%20than%20others.%20In%20July%2C%20the%20Economic%20Innovation%20Group%2C%20a%20centrist%20think-tank%2C%20published%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feig.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FTAWP-Kirkegaard.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Jacob%20Funk%20Kirkegaard%2C%20a%20nonresident%20fellow%20with%20the%20Peterson%20Institute%20for%20International%20Economics.%20Using%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20and%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%2C%20the%20analysis%20highlighted%20the%20average%20annual%20wages%20across%20US%20states%20as%20of%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMississippi%20had%20the%20second%20lowest%20average%20annual%20wage%20in%20the%20US%20at%20roughly%20%2460%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20only%20Hawaii%20ranked%20lower.%20Texas%20was