k-valuation-seen-at-around-4-4-billion-124072700431_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ola%20is%20planning%20the%20IPO%20at%20a%20lower%20valuation%20to%20ensure%20higher%20participation%20from%20investors%20bidding%20for%20the%20IPO%20shares%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fipo%2Fola-electric-to-launch-ipo-next-week-valuation-seen-at-around-4-4-billion-124072700431_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fipo%2Fola-electric-to-launch-ipo-next-week-valuation-seen-at-around-4-4-billion-124072700431_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fipo%2Fola-electric-to-launch-ipo-next-week-valuation-seen-at-around-4-4-billion-124072700431_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Are%20'Documented%20Dreamers'%20And%20Why%20Are%20They%20Facing%20Deportation%20From%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENearly%202%2C50%2C000%20children%20of%20legal%20immigrants%2C%20including%20a%20significantly%20large%20number%20of%20Indian-Americans%2C%20are%20now%20facing%20a%20major%20risk%20of%20being%20deported%20from%20the%20US%20after%20they%20turned%2021%20and%20%26quot%3Baged%20out%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalled%20the%20'%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fdocumented-dreamers-children-of-indian-american-immigrants-face-deportation-as-time-runs-out-6189959%5C%22%3Edocumented%20dreamers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C'%20these%20people%20enter%20the%20US%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20who%20are%20usually%20on%20temporary%20work%20visas.%20However%2C%20they%20lose%20their%20temporary%20dependent%20status%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20turn%2021%20and%20face%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20analysis%20of%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20(USCIS)%20data%20by%20the%20National%20Foundation%20for%20American%20Policy%2C%20more%20than%201.2%20million%20Indians%2C%20including%20dependents%2C%20have%20been%20waiting%20in%20the%20first%2C%20second%2C%20and%20third%20employment-based%20green%20card%20categories%20as%20of%20November%202%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EWho%20are%20documented%20dreamers%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minor%20children%20coming%20to%20the%20US%20through%20the%20temporary%2C%20non-immigrant%20visa%20category%20along%20with%20their%20parents%20remain%20eligible%20to%20obtain%20permanent%20resident%20status%20through%20a%20parent%20if%20it%20occurs%20before%20they%20turn%2021.%20However%2C%20if%20they%20fail%20to%20attain%20permanent%20residency%20before%20the%20mentioned%20age%2C%20these%20children%20lose%20their%20temporary%20dependent%20status%20and%20are%20thereby%20removed%20from%20the%20green%20card%20queue%20--%20in%20official%20terms%20they%20age%20out%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanimmigrationcouncil.org%2Fresearch%2Fdocumented-dreamers-overview%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Immigration%20%3C%2Fa%3ECouncil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20turn%2021%2C%20the%20children%20%E2%80%9Cage%20out%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20temporary%20legal%20status%20derived%20through%20their%20parents'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fstuartanderson%2F2024%2F04%2F14%2Fmore-than-1-million-indians-waiting-for-high-skilled-immigrant-visas%2F%5C%22%3Evisas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20face%20potential%20deportation%20unless%20they%20can%20obtain%20a%20different%20temporary%20or%20permanent%20status%20by%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20popular%20H-1B%20visa%2C%20one%20of%20the%20widely%20utilized%20categories%20in%20temporary%20visas%2C%20allows%20the%20minor%20children%20of%20an%20individual%20in%20H-1B%20status%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20as%20H-4%20dependents%20--%20a%20temporary%2C%20non-immigrant%20visa%20category%20allowing%20them%20legal%20status%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20country%20for%20a%20limited%20period%20of%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20do%20they%20face%20deportation%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20they%20reach%2021%2C%20these%20'Documented%20Dreamers'%20remain%20excluded%20from%20the%20temporary%20deportation%20protections%20as%20well%20as%20work%20authorisation%20afforded%20to%20them%20through%20the%20Deferred%20Action%20for%20Childhood%20Arrivals%20(DACA)%20initiative.%20This%20requires%20the%20recipients%20to%20have%20%E2%80%9Cno%20lawful%20status%20on%20June%2015%2C%202012%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Council%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20these%20children%20do%20not%20have%20legal%20status%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20US%2C%20they%20are%20required%20to%20transition%20to%20a%20new%20temporary%20status%20or%20self-deport%20as%20they%20become%20undocumented%20and%20risk%20being%20subjected%20to%20enforcement%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20exercise%20of%20prosecutorial%20discretion%2C%20DACA%20gives%20temporary%20relief%20from%20deportation%20and%20work%20authorisation%20to%20a%20particular%20group%20of%20undocumented%20immigrants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20does%20not%20provide%20permanent%20legal%20status%20to%20individuals%20and%20has%20to%20be%20renewed%20every%20two%20years.%20In%20order%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20this%2C%20the%20applications%20have%20to%20meet%20certain%20requirements%2C%20including%20the%20significant%20one%20that%20requires%20the%20person%20to%20have%20%E2%80%9Chad%20no%20lawful%20status%20on%20June%2015%2C%202012.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20majority%20of%20cases%2C%20this%20requirement%20disqualifies%20the%20'Documented%20Dreamers'%2C%20who%20generally%20have%20lawful%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20does%20the%20US%20government%20say%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20White%20House%20blamed%20the%20Republicans%20for%20this%20legislative%20impasse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20talked%20about%20the%20bipartisan%20agreement%20that%20came%20together%20from%20the%20Senate%20where%20we%20negotiated%20a%20process%20to%20help%20the%20so-called%20documented%20Dreamers.%20And%20sadly%2C%20Republicans%2C%20and%20I've%20said%20this%20many%20times%20already%20at%20this%20podium%20today%2C%20which%20is%20that%20they%20voted%20it%20down%20twice%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20House%20Press%20Secretary%20Karine%20Jean-Pierre%20said%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20a%20bipartisan%20group%20of%2043%20lawmakers%2C%20led%20by%20Senator%20Alex%20Padilla%2C%20called%20on%20the%20Joe%20Biden-led%20administration%20to%20take%20urgent%20action%20to%20protect%20these%20Documented%20Dreamers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...due%20to%20the%20long%20green-card%20backlog%2C%20families%20with%20approved%20immigrant%20petitions%20are%20often%20stuck%20waiting%20decades%20for%20permanent%20resident%20status%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said%20in%20the%20June%2013%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722071340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2Fus-immigration_625x300_1529135127346.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fwho-are-documented-dreamers-and-why-are-they-facing-deportation-from-us-6199547%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nearly%202%2C50%2C000%20children%20of%20legal%20immigrants%2C%20including%20a%20significantly%20large%20number%20of%20Indian-Americans%2C%20are%20now%20facing%20a%20major%20risk%20of%20being%20deported%20from%20the%20US%20after%20they%20turned%2021%20and%20%26quot%3Baged%20out%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fwho-are-documented-dreamers-and-why-are-they-facing-deportation-from-us-6199547%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fwho-are-documented-dreamers-and-why-are-they-facing-deportation-from-us-6199547%2Fam